      <h1 class="govuk-heading-l">Apply for a farming grant terms and conditions: 7 February to 13 June 2023</h1>
      <p class="govuk-body">
        These terms and conditions cover agreements made from 7 February 2023 up to and including 13 June 2023.
      </p>
      <h2 class="govuk-heading-m">1. Introduction</h2>
      <h3 class="govuk-heading-s">1.1 The Annual Health and Welfare Review</h3>
      <p class="govuk-body">
        The Annual Health and Welfare Review (“AHWR”) is a scheme run by the Rural Payments Agency (referred to below as “us,
        “we”, “our”) on behalf of the Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs (“Defra”). The AWHR is a financial
        assistance scheme under section 1 of the Agriculture Act 2020 and is in conjunction with the Agriculture (Financial
        Assistance) Regulations 2021 (“the Regulations”) amended by The Agriculture (Financial Assistance) (Amendment)
        Regulations 2022.
      </p>
      <h3 class="govuk-heading-s">1.2 About these Terms and Conditions</h3>
      <ol class="govuk-list--alphabet govuk-body">
        <li>The AHWR Beta 2 agreement (the “Agreement”) comprises these “Terms and Conditions”, which are applicable to the
          payment of the one-off sum (the “Payment”) to the agreement holder (“you”)</li>
        <li>The Terms and Conditions only apply to Beta 2 of the AHWR Private Beta (“Beta 2”) for a review of the health and
          welfare (“Review”) of a single herd or flock (a epidemiologically distinct unit of a single species) of beef cattle or
          dairy cattle, or sheep, or pigs (the “Single Species”).</li>
      </ol>
      <h3 class="govuk-heading-s">1.3 References in the Terms and Conditions</h3>
      <ol class="govuk-list--alphabet govuk-body">
        <li>Definitions of capitalised terms are defined in this document when they are first referred to.</li>
        <li>A reference to the “Law” means any law, statute, subordinate legislation within the meaning of Section 21(1) of the
          Interpretation Act 1978, byelaw, right within the meaning of Section 4(1) EU Withdrawal Act 2018 as amended by EU
          (Withdrawal Agreement) Act 2020, regulation, order, regulatory policy, mandatory guidance or code of practice, judgement
          of a relevant court of law, or directives or requirements of any regulatory body with which you are required to comply.</li>
        <li>A reference to a statute or statutory provision is a reference to it as amended, extended or re-enacted from time to
          time and shall include all subordinate legislation made under that statute or statutory provision.</li>
        <li>A reference to a public organisation includes a reference to any successor to that public organisation.</li>
        <li>Any words following the terms ‘including’, ‘include’, ‘in particular’ or ‘for example’ or any similar phrase shall
          be construed as illustrative and shall not limit the generality of the related general words.</li>
        <li>Unless the context otherwise requires, words in the singular shall include the plural and in the plural shall
          include the singular.</li>
      </ol>
      <h3 class="govuk-heading-s">1.4 Beta 2 guidance</h3>
      <p class="govuk-body">We have set out further information about a Review under Beta 2 in accompanying guidance. This
        guidance is there to help you and will not be used to introduce or explain mandatory requirements of your Agreement.</p>
      <h2 class="govuk-heading-m">2. About your Agreement</h2>
      <h3 class="govuk-heading-s">2.1 Your Agreement</h3>
      <p class="govuk-body">The Agreement comprises these Terms and Conditions (which are further explained in the Beta 2
        guidance as referred to in condition 1.4).</p>
      <h3 class="govuk-heading-s">2.2 What you are declaring</h3>
      <p class="govuk-body">By entering the Agreement you confirm that:</p>
      <ol class="govuk-list--alphabet govuk-body">
        <li>you are registered with us and have a valid and current Single Business Identifier (SBI);</li>
        <li>the SBI referred to in condition 2.2(a) is linked to at least one permanent or temporary County Parish Holding (CPH)
          number that is registered in England only and which is not an 8000 series CPH number or a 9000 series CPH number;</li>
        <li>you are the person responsible for a Single Species on a permanent or temporary basis on the date or dates the Vet
          carries out the Review;</li>
        <li>you will have the relevant minimum number of the Single Species as described in condition 3.3 on the date or dates
          the Vet carries out the Review;</li>
        <li>You will have the relevant minimum number of Single Species as described in condition 4.1 on the date or dates the
          Vet carries out the testing for the Review.</li>
        <li>you will only apply for a Review under Beta 2 and receive the Payment for a Single Species;</li>
        <li>the Single Species is registered in England;</li>
        <li>the declarations you made in your Beta 2 application for the Payment remain true and accurate to the best of your
          knowledge and belief;</li>
        <li>you have full capacity and authority to enter into the Agreement;</li>
        <li>you are not aware of any circumstances which would render you ineligible for the Payment or otherwise prevent you
          from complying with your obligations under the Agreement;</li>
        <li>your obligations under the Agreement do not and will not conflict in whole or in part with any other legal or
          contractual obligations you are subject to; and</li>
        <li>you will at all times comply with all relevant Law in the performance of your obligations under the Agreement</li>
      </ol>
      <h3 class="govuk-heading-s">2.3 What you are agreeing to do</h3>
      <p class="govuk-body">In applying for Beta 2 and receiving the Payment, you are agreeing to:</p>
      <ol class="govuk-list--alphabet govuk-body">
        <li>comply with these Terms and Conditions; and</li>
        <li>use the Payment for the purpose of undertaking the requirements of Beta 2 as set out in these Terms and Conditions.</li>
      </ol>
      <h3 class="govuk-heading-s">2.4 Agreement Period
      </h3>
      <ol class="govuk-list--alphabet govuk-body">
        <li>The Agreement is for a period of six (6) months from the date, you accept our offer (“Agreement Start Date”) until
          the expiry of those 6 months (“Agreement End Date”),</li>
        <li>The Agreement Start Date and Agreement End Date are shown on the agreement summary referred to in condition 6.2.</li>
      </ol>
      <h2 class="govuk-heading-m">3. A Review under Beta 2
      </h2>
      <p class="govuk-body">3.1 You must ask a Royal College of Veterinary Surgeons (RCVS) registered vet (“Vet”) to complete
        a Review of the Single Species under Beta 2.</p>
      <p class="govuk-body">3.2 You must tell the Vet about the requirements for a Review under Beta 2, there is accompanying
        Beta 2 Vet guidance that will assist the Vet to carry out this AWHR. It is your responsibility to make sure that the
        Review completed by the Vet complies with these Terms and Conditions.</p>
      <p class="govuk-body">3.3 You must have the following minimum number of the relevant Single Species present on the date
        or dates the Vet carries out the Review:</p>
      <ol class="govuk-list--alphabet govuk-body">
        <li>At least 11 dairy cattle.</li>
        <li>At least 11 beef cattle.</li>
        <li>At least 21 sheep.</li>
        <li>At least 51 pigs.</li>
      </ol>
      <p class="govuk-body">3.4 To complete a Review under Beta 2, you must ask the Vet to do all of the following:</p>
      <ol class="govuk-list--alphabet govuk-body">
        <li>visit the relevant Single Species and carry out the tests to the relevant minimum number of Single Species required
          for testing as described in condition 4.1. The minimum number of Single Species required for testing under condition 4.1
          is different to the minimum number set out in condition 3.3 above, you must comply with both.</li>
        <li>send the relevant test samples from the tests described in condition 4.1 to a laboratory for analysis;</li>
        <li>conduct a review of the general health and welfare of the relevant Single Species;</li>
        <li>provide you with the relevant test results from the tests described in condition 4.1, including the detailed
          laboratory analysis;</li>
        <li>provide you with a written report (the “Report”) and you must ask the Vet to follow the Beta 2 guidance setting out
          what should be in the Report;</li>
        <li>provide you with a separate review summary sheet (the “Review Summary Sheet”) as described in condition 5 to
          accompany the Report referred to in condition 3.4(e).</li>
      </ol>
      <h2 class="govuk-heading-m">4. Testing a Single Species
      </h2>
      <p class="govuk-body">4.1 You must ask the Vet to carry out one (1) of the following tests of the relevant minimum
        number of the relevant Single Species on the date or dates the Vet carries out the Review:</h3>
      <ol class="govuk-list--alphabet govuk-body">
        <li>test at least five (5) beef cattle for Bovine Viral Diarrhoea (BVD) using a blood (serum) antibody test;</li>
        <li>test any number of dairy cattle for BVD using an antibody bulk milk test or a polymerase chain reaction (PCR) bulk
          milk test or a blood (serum) antibody test;</li>
        <li>test at least ten (10) sheep for the effectiveness of worming treatments containing one (1) of the following active
          chemicals:</li>
        <ul class="govuk-list">
          <li>i. Benzimidazole (BZ)</li>
          <li>ii. Levamisole (LV)</li>
          <li>iii. Macrocyclic lactones (ML)</li>
          <li>iv. Amino-acetonitrile derivatives (AD)
          </li>
          <li>v. Spiroindoles (SI)
          </li>
        </ul>
        <li>test at least thirty (30) pigs for Porcine Reproductive and Respiratory Syndrome (PRRS) using an enzyme-linked
          immunosorbent assay (ELISA) or PRRS PCR test.</li>
      </ol>
      <p class="govuk-body">4.2 The tests set out in condition 4.1 are in addition to any other services which you may agree
        for the Vet to provide at the same time as the Review, but which are not covered by the Payment.</p>
      <p class="govuk-body">4.3 You must ask the Vet to send the samples from the tests set out in condition 4.1 to a suitably
        accredited laboratory for the relevant analysis, the Vet guidance has further information on what a suitably accredited
        laboratory for each Single Species will be.</p>
      <p class="govuk-body">4.4 You must ask the Vet to share the results analysis received from the laboratory explained in
        condition 4.3 for the relevant tests set out in condition 4.1.</p>
      <p class="govuk-body">4.5 You cannot use test results you have already obtained under another accreditation scheme or
        any other legal or contractual obligation you are subject to in order to meet the testing requirements set out in
        condition 4.1.</p>
      <h2 class="govuk-heading-m">5. Review Summary Sheet</h2>
      <p class="govuk-body">5.1 The Review Summary Sheet referred to in condition 3.4(f) must include all of the following:
      </p>
      <ol class="govuk-list--alphabet govuk-body">
        <li>the unique reference number for your Agreement;
        </li>
        <li>your business name and SBI;
        </li>
        <li>the last date the Vet visited your CPH for the Review.</li>
        <li>the Single Species you selected for the Review under Beta 2;</li>
        <li>confirmation that you had the required minimum numbers of Single Species in accordance with condition 3.3</li>
        <li>confirmation that the Vet completed the testing in accordance with condition 4.1;</li>
        <li>the unique reference number for the laboratory test results under condition 4.4;</li>
        <li>confirmation that the Vet provided you with a Report as referred to in condition 3;</li>
        <li>the RCVS-registered reference number for the Vet; and</li>
        <li>the signature of the Vet and the date the Vet signed the Review Summary Sheet.</li>
      </ol>
      <h2 class="govuk-heading-m">6. Applying for a Review</h2>
      <p class="govuk-body">6.1 To apply for a Review of a Single Species you must:</p>
      <ol class="govuk-list--alphabet govuk-body">
        <li>confirm that you meet the eligibility criteria.</li>
        <li>confirm that you will carry out the required actions.</li>
        <li>confirm that you have read, understood and accept these Terms and Conditions.</li>
        <li>submit your Beta 2 application</li>
      </ol>
      <p class="govuk-body">If we approve your Beta 2 application under condition 6.1, we will offer you an Agreement which
        you must either accept or reject.</p>
      <p class="govuk-body">6.2 If you accept the Agreement, we will share an agreement summary with you which will confirm:</p>
      <ol class="govuk-list--alphabet govuk-body">
        <li>the unique reference number (URN) for the Agreement, which you should use in any correspondence with us;</li>
        <li>the Agreement Start Date and Agreement End Date;</li>
        <li>your business name and SBI; and</li>
        <li>the selected Single Species for the Review.</li>
      </ol>
      <p class="govuk-body">6.3 You must not ask the Vet to complete the Review under condition 3 until you accept the
        Agreement. The Review must not start until the Agreement Start Date.</p>
      <p class="govuk-body">6.4 You cannot apply for a further Review of a Single Species until ten (10) months after the
        Agreement Start Date.</p>
      <p class="govuk-body">6.5 For the duration of Beta 2, as long as you have complied with these Terms and Conditions you
        can apply for up to a maximum of three (3) Reviews of a Single Species subject to 6.4.</p>
      <h2 class="govuk-heading-m">7. Payment</h2>
      <p class="govuk-body">7.1 The Payment rates for completing a Review under Beta 2 of a Single Species as described in
        Condition 3, as relevant, are:</p>
      <ol class="govuk-list--alphabet govuk-body">
        <li>£522 for a Review of beef cattle</li>
        <li>£372 for a Review of dairy cattle</li>
        <li>£436 for a Review of sheep</li>
        <li>£684 for a Review of pigs</li>
      </ol>
      <p class="govuk-body">7.2 It is your responsibility to pay the Vet. If the amount the Vet charges you for the Review
        exceeds the amount of Payment that you are eligible to receive, you will be responsible for the excess amount.</p>
      <p class="govuk-body">7.3 To be eligible for the Payment, no more than six (6) months after your Agreement Start date
        you must (subject to condition 7.14):</p>
      <ol class="govuk-list--alphabet govuk-body">
        <li>make sure the Vet completes the Review in accordance with condition 3; and</li>
        <li>complete and submit your Payment claim</li>
      </ol>
      <p class="govuk-body">7.4 When you have carried out the actions required under condition 7.3, we will use reasonable
        endeavours to make the associated Payment no later than twenty-eight (28) days after verifying your Payment claim is
        valid and meets these Terms and Conditions, subject to any limitation on Payments under condition 16.2</p>
      <p class="govuk-body">7.5 We will make the Payment directly to the bank or building society account that is registered
        with us for the SBI referred to under condition 2.2(b) via BACS transfer, subject to the necessary funds being available
        when the Payment falls due.</p>
      <p class="govuk-body">7.6 We reserve the right to withhold, delay, reduce or recover, the Payment or require repayment
        of all or part of the Payment if you fail to comply with any of these Terms and Conditions.</p>
      <p class="govuk-body">7.7 We reserve the right to withhold, delay, reduce, or recover the Payment or require repayment
        of all or part of the Payment if you;</p>
      <ol class="govuk-list--alphabet govuk-body">
        <li>defraud, mislead or provide false information to us,</li>
        <li>fail to comply with condition 8</li>
        <li>if you fail to comply with the Law</li>
      </ol>
      <p class="govuk-body">7.8 If we inform you that you have received a Payment which does not meet the requirements of
        these Terms and Conditions, you must repay us any such amounts within sixty (60) days of the date of our demand for
        repayment.</p>
      <p class="govuk-body">7.9 Any sum that becomes repayable under condition 7.8 will be treated as a debt by you to us and
        if it is not repaid we may issue a recovery order in respect of it.</p>
      <p class="govuk-body">7.10 Before taking any action under condition 7.6, condition 7.7 or condition 7.8 we will assess
        all the circumstances of a breach in a fair and consistent manner and take action as appropriate</p>
      <p class="govuk-body">7.11 You may withdraw your claim for Payment at any time by giving us written notice of your wish
        to withdraw subject to condition 7.12. This does not prevent you from resubmitting your claim subject to condition
        2.4(a). In the event of withdrawal, any Payment already made to you, shall be fully repayable to us.</p>
      <p class="govuk-body">7.12 You may not withdraw your claim:</p>
      <ol class="govuk-list--alphabet govuk-body">
        <li>in the event that we have informed you of a breach of this Agreement; or</li>
        <li>where we have given you notice of a suspected breach of this Agreement; or</li>
        <li>where we have asked you to send us any evidence in relation to your compliance with this Agreement</li>
      </ol>
      <p class="govuk-body">7.13 If you fail to comply with condition 7.3 you will be in breach of your Agreement. We
        understand that there may be circumstances where you are in breach of condition 7.3(b) because of events outside of your
        control (a “Good Reason”).</p>
      <p class="govuk-body">7.14.1 If you breach condition 7.3(b) for a Good Reason, you (or any person authorised to act for
        you) must notify us in writing to explain the Good Reason. If we determine that there is a Good Reason for the breach of
        your Agreement you may still be eligible for the Payment You must notify us:</p>
      <p class="govuk-body">7.14.2 in writing within eight (8) weeks from:</p>
      <ol class="govuk-list--alphabet govuk-body">
        <li>the date you are able to; or</li>
        <li>the date we notify you of the Determination on the breach of the Agreement</li>
      </ol>
      <p class="govuk-body">7.15 A decision about whether you are still eligible for the Payment under 7.14 will be at our
        sole discretion and you may be asked to provide further evidence to support your Good Reason for the breach of your
        Agreement.</p>
      <p class="govuk-body">7.16 Condition 7.14 does not apply if you are in breach of condition 7.3(a).</p>
      <h2 class="govuk-heading-m">8. Record-keeping</h2>
      <p class="govuk-body">8.1 You must keep all invoices, receipts, the Review Summary Sheet, accounts and any other
        relevant documents relating directly to the expenditure of the Payment and evidence of your compliance with your
        obligations under these Terms and Conditions (“Records”).</p>
      <p class="govuk-body">8.2 You must keep your Records for a period of at least seven (7) years from the Agreement End
        Date.</p>
      <p class="govuk-body">8.3 You must prepare and keep your Records in compliance with Law and must provide assistance to
        us when we are auditing or examining these so as to help us carry out our legal obligations.</p>
      <p class="govuk-body">8.4 We have the right to:</p>
      <ol class="govuk-list--alphabet govuk-body">
        <li>request you to provide your Records to us</li>
        <li>review your Records</li>
        <li>take copies of such Records</li>
      </ol>
      <p class="govuk-body">8.5 You must provide your Records to us upon request. In addition, you shall provide the Records
        to any other duly authorised public authority (or their authorised representatives or auditors) upon request.</p>
      <p class="govuk-body">8.6 If you do not provide your Records on request this may result in your Payment being declined
        or withheld.</p>
      <h2 class="govuk-heading-m">9. Data Protection</h2>
      <p class="govuk-body">9.1 We and you must always comply with any respective obligations under “Data Protection
        Legislation”. We may be required to provide personal information to Defra. Data Protection Legislation means (a) the UK
        GDPR, (b) the Data Protection Act 2018 to the extent that it relates to processing of personal data and privacy and (c)
        all applicable Law about the processing of personal data and privacy.</p>
      <p class="govuk-body">9.2 UK GDPR means Regulation (EU) 2016/679 of the European Parliament and of the Council of 27
        April 2016 on the protection of natural persons with regard to the processing of personal data and on the free movement
        of such data (General Data Protection Regulation) (United Kingdom General Data Protection Regulation), as it forms part
        of the law of England and Wales, Scotland and Northern Ireland by virtue of section 3 of the European Union (Withdrawal)
        Act 2018 (and see section 205(4)).</p>
      <p class="govuk-body">9.3 For information on how we handle personal data search for
        <a
          href="https://www.gov.uk/government/organisations/rural-payments-agency/about/personal-information-charter"
          target="_blank">'Rural Payments Agency Personal Information Charter'</a>
        and our
        <a href="https://www.gov.uk/guidance/rpa-privacy-notices" target="_blank">Privacy Policy</a>
        on GOV.UK.</p>
      <h2 class="govuk-heading-m">10. Freedom of Information</h2>
      <p class="govuk-body">10.1 You acknowledge that we are subject to the requirements of the Freedom of Information Act
        2000 ("FOIA") and the Environmental Information Regulations 2004 ("EIR")</p>
      <p class="govuk-body">10.2 We may need to share information it holds about you or the conditions of payment so we or
        Defra can comply with any FOIA and EIR request. The extent, content and format of the information we disclose is our
        decision. In making any disclosure, we will have due regard to Data Protection Legislation.</p>
      <p class="govuk-body">10.3 You will provide all necessary assistance and cooperation which we or Defra reasonably
        request for the purposes of complying with our obligations under FOIA and EIR within a time period specified by us. You
        must tell us as soon as reasonably practicable if you receive a FOIA or EIR request intended for us or Defra.</p>
      <h2 class="govuk-heading-m">11. Termination</h2>
      <p class="govuk-body">11.1 We may terminate the Agreement before the Agreement End Date on written notice to you:</p>
      <ol class="govuk-list--alphabet govuk-body">
        <li>if you have breached the Terms and Conditions of the Agreement.</li>
        <li>if you have not repaid to us a sum that has become recoverable under condition 7.</li>
        <li>at any time on at least six (6) weeks written notice to you. You may be required to repay all or part of the Payment
          and you will remain bound by the relevant obligations under the Agreement until you make this repayment. This will only
          be utilised in limited circumstances.</li>
      </ol>
      <p class="govuk-body">11.2.1 You may terminate the agreement on written notice to us:</p>
      <ol class="govuk-list--alphabet govuk-body">
        <li>for any reason; or</li>
        <li>as set out in condition 13.3.</li>
      </ol>
      <p class="govuk-body">11.2.2 In the event you exercise your right to termination set out in 11.2.1 (a) you must keep a
        record of your reasons for termination and comply with condition 8</p>
      <p class="govuk-body">11.2.3 You may not exercise your right to termination under 11.2.1 (a):</p>
      <ol class="govuk-list--alphabet govuk-body">
        <li>in the event that we have informed you of a breach of this Agreement; or</li>
        <li>where we have given you notice of a suspected breach of this Agreement; or</li>
        <li>where we have asked you to send us any evidence in relation to your compliance with this Agreement</li>
      </ol>
      <p class="govuk-body">11.2.4 Should you exercise your termination right under this condition 11.2, you will not receive
        the Payment and we accept no liability for any costs you may have incurred prior to termination.</p>
      <p class="govuk-body">11.2.5 If a Vet has carried out a Review of a Single Species under this Agreement prior to
        termination and you exercise your termination right under this condition 11.2 you will not be able to reapply for
        Payment and a further Review of the same Single Species.</p>
      <p class="govuk-body">11.2.6 Any Payment already made to you, shall be fully repayable to us if you terminate this
        Agreement under this condition 11.2. You shall make any payments due to us without any deduction whether by way of
        set-off, counterclaim, discount, abatement or otherwise</p>
      <p class="govuk-body">11.3 Termination or expiry of the Agreement will not affect our or your continuing rights and
        obligations under any condition in the Agreement which is intended to continue beyond the Agreement End Date (such as
        Record keeping).</p>
      <p class="govuk-body">11.4 In the event you terminate in line with condition 11.2, and condition 11.2.5 does not apply
        to you, condition 6.4 shall be waived.</p>
      <h2 class="govuk-heading-m">12. Third Party Rights</h2>
      <p class="govuk-body">The Agreement is between you and us. No other person shall have any rights to enforce any of its
        terms, however, the terms of the Agreement and our rights under it may be enforced by Defra.</p>
      <h2 class="govuk-heading-m">13. Variation</h2>
      <p class="govuk-body">13.1 We may need to vary your Agreement before the Agreement End Date, we will only do this where
        there are exceptional circumstances, such as:</p>
      <ol class="govuk-list--alphabet govuk-body">
        <li>changes in Law which must be reflected in the Agreement;</li>
        <li>the need to respond to wider government emergency measures and/or measures imperative to the national interest, for
          example, disease outbreaks or food security emergencies.</li>
      </ol>
      <p class="govuk-body">13.2 If we need to vary your Agreement as set out in condition 13.1, we will notify you in writing
        setting out the required variation/s and will endeavour to give such notice as is reasonable and proportionate, having
        regard to the nature of the variation and its consequences for you.</p>
      <p class="govuk-body">13.3 You will be able to terminate the Agreement if you do not agree with the variation to the
        Agreement set out in 13.2 subject to 11.3.</p>
      <h2 class="govuk-heading-m">14. Reconsideration of Determinations</h2>
      <p class="govuk-body">14.1 If you would like us to reconsider any determination that we have made following a breach by
        you of the Agreement ("Determination") you should use our
        <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/organisations/rural-payments-agency/about/complaints-procedure" target="_blank">
        complaints procedure</a>
        to ask for it to be reconsidered.</p>
      <p class="govuk-body">14.2 You must ask us to reconsider any Determination within sixty (60) calendar days of the date
        you are notified about our Determination.</p>
      <p class="govuk-body">14.3 We will consider your request to reconsider our Determination carefully, including any
        information or evidence you have provided to us. We will confirm our outcome of our reconsideration, with reasons, in
        writing within a reasonable period.</p>
      <p class="govuk-body">14.4 You may appeal the outcome of our reconsideration of our Determination within sixty (60)
        calendar days of the date you are notified of that outcome where you believe the outcome of our reconsideration:</p>
      <ol class="govuk-list--alphabet govuk-body">
        <li>was based on an error of fact;</li>
        <li>was wrong in Law; or</li>
        <li>there has been a material procedural error.</li>
      </ol>
      <p class="govuk-body">14.5 We will confirm the outcome of your appeal under condition 14.4 within a reasonable period in
        writing explaining the reasons for this outcome, and this will be our final determination.</p>
      <h2 class="govuk-heading-m">15. Monitoring and Evaluation</h2>
      <p class="govuk-body">15.1 You acknowledge that as a condition of receiving the Payment you may be required to
        participate in an evaluation, which may take place during the agreement period (the Agreement Start Date to the
